definitions: (in nuclear physics) containing or involving more than the critical mass.
shortDefinitions: (in nuclear physics) containing or involving more than critical mass

definitions: (of a flow of fluid) faster than the speed at which waves travel in the fluid.
shortDefinitions: (of flow of fluid) faster than speed at which waves travel in fluid

definitions: denoting an airfoil or aircraft wing designed to tolerate shock-wave formation at transonic speeds.
shortDefinitions: denoting aerofoil or aircraft wing designed to tolerate shock-wave formation at transonic speeds

definitions: relating to or denoting a fluid at a temperature and pressure greater than its critical temperature and pressure.
shortDefinitions: of fluid at temperature and pressure greater than its critical temperature
